    "en": {
      "title": "European ministers to cut gas for winter",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "EU member states have agreed to voluntarily cut gas consumption by 15% this winter after energy ministers met in Brussels on Tuesday.",
        "The agreement also includes a special mechanism called \"Union Alert\" which mandates reduction of consumption in case of emergency. This can only be implemented after the approval of the European Council, which is made up of the leaders of the EU member states.",
        "\"By working together to reduce demand for gas, taking into account all relevant national specificities, the EU has secured a solid basis for the much-needed cooperation between member states in the face of Putin's energy blackmail,\" European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen said in a statement."
      ],
